# Audio Signal Processor in Docker 🎶

This project provides a Python script to **load, manipulate, and visualize audio signals**.  
It runs inside a **Docker container**, so you don’t need to install Python, ffmpeg, or other dependencies.

---

## ✨ Features

- Load a `.wav` audio file  
- Generate and save:
  - Waveform plots  
  - Spectrograms  
- Apply a simple **echo effect**  
- Save the processed audio to a new `.wav` file  
- Save waveform plots of the processed audio  

---

## 📂 Project Structure

/
├── Dockerfile # Build instructions for Docker
├── README.md # This file
├── audio_processor.py # Main Python script
├── requirements.txt # Python dependencies
└── your_audio_file.wav # Input audio file (replace with your own)

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- **Docker** (make sure the Docker engine is running).  
  👉 [Download Docker](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop)

---

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone <your-repository-url>
cd <repository-name>

2. Add Your Audio File

Place your .wav file in the project root.

Rename it to your_audio_file.wav (or update the filename in audio_processor.py).
